## Commands

```bash
npm install          # Install dependencies
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Production build
npm test             # Run test suite
npm run lint         # Lint check
npm run lint -- --fix # Auto-fix lint issues
```

## Architecture

- `src/` — Application source code
- `tests/` — Test files (mirror src/ structure)
- `package.json` — Dependencies and scripts

## Code Style

- ES modules (import/export), not CommonJS (require)
- Destructure imports: `import { foo } from 'bar'`
- TypeScript strict mode where applicable
- Max 200 lines per file, max 50 lines per function

## Testing

- Run single test files, not full suite, during development
- Prefer `describe`/`it` blocks with descriptive names
- No mocks unless testing external services

## Security

- Never commit `.env`, API keys, or credentials
- Reference secrets by env var name only
- Use `process.env.VAR_NAME` with fallback defaults

## AI Workflow

- Every feature: **Spec → Plan → Code → Test → Refactor** — never skip spec/plan
- One module at a time (narrow slices) — no big-bang system generation
- Never accept first output — run a critique pass before committing
- Always run code locally before claiming done — paste exact errors, not descriptions
- `/clear` after ~20 file reads or major topic shifts

